    "Apart from enhanced coverage, CHATAFL discovered nine previously unknown vulnerabilities in widely-used protocol implementations, the majority of which could not be found by AFLNET and NSFUZZ.",
    "We start by introducing the main technical concepts in protocol fuzzing and elucidating the key open challenges that we seek to address in this paper.",
    "We then provide some background on large language models and our motivation.",
    "A. Protocol FuzzingIn order to facilitate the systematic and reliable exchange of information on the Internet, all participants agree to use a common protocol.",
    "Many of the most widely-used protocols have been designed by the Internet Engineering Task Force (IETF) and published as Request for Comments (RFC)."
